# Stability Studio — guided onboarding

This MCP is **not** a one-click installer. It helps **less technical users** use ComfyUI through an AI assistant.

## When to run onboarding

- User asks to install, set up, get started, or "how does this work"
- First session on a fresh clone
- User seems unsure what they can generate

## Agent steps

1. Call **`get_onboarding_context`** (or read `onboarding/ONBOARDING.md` + `onboarding/CHECKLIST.yaml`).
2. Ask **2–4 discovery questions** (goal, GPU/VRAM, ComfyUI experience, art style) — see checklist `discovery_questions`.
3. Pick the **lowest tier** that fits; do not jump to storyboard or Wan2GP early.
4. State the **disclaimer**: large downloads, NVIDIA GPU, restarts are normal.

## VRAM routing (strict)

| VRAM | Policy |
|------|--------|
| **≥ 24 GB** | **ComfyUI only** — do not offer Wan2GP unless user is blocked |
| **16–23 GB** | ComfyUI default; Wan2GP only if user explicitly wants hero/lip sync |
| **≤ 16 GB** | ComfyUI images + draft video; Wan2GP = optional Tier 4 |

## Tiers (do not skip gates)

| Tier | Goal |
|------|------|
| 0 | Browse `onboarding/examples/rin/` — no GPU |
| 1 | Still images — Stability Matrix + ComfyUI |
| 2 | Draft video — `i2v_5b` / `t2v` smoke test |
| 3 | Storyboard — MOSS + project folders + splice |
| 4 | Hero / lip sync — Wan2GP opt-in only |

## First win

Always aim for one small success before max quality (one `generate_image` or 17-frame video).

## Failures

See `onboarding/TROUBLESHOOTING.md`. Restart ComfyUI after node installs and large downloads.
